<exercise checkit-seed="0021" checkit-slug="V7" checkit-title="Basis of a subspace">
  <statement>
    <p>Consider the subspace <me>W=\operatorname{span}  \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \\
-1 \\
1 \\
0
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \\
0 \\
3 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
3 \\
3 \\
2
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
12 \\
1 \\
-7 \\
2
\end{array}\right] \right\} .</me></p>
    <ol>
      <li> Explain how to find a basis of <m>W</m>.</li>
      <li> Explain how to find the dimension of <m>W</m>.</li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <p>
      <me>\operatorname{RREF} \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-4 &amp; -4 &amp; 3 &amp; 12 \\
-1 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 &amp; 1 \\
1 &amp; 3 &amp; 3 &amp; -7 \\
0 &amp; -1 &amp; 2 &amp; 2
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; -1 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me>
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>A basis of <m>W</m> is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \\
-1 \\
1 \\
0
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \\
0 \\
3 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
3 \\
3 \\
2
\end{array}\right] \right\} </m>.</li>
      <li>The dimension of <m>W</m> is <m> 3 </m>.</li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

